  "prompt": "What hand drawn anime is out there?",
  "response": "There are several notable hand-drawn anime series and films that are celebrated for their artistry and attention to detail. Here are some examples:\n\n### Anime Series:\n\n1. **Fullmetal Alchemist: Brotherhood**\n   - Known for its detailed character designs and fluid animation, this series has a strong following and is considered one of the best hand-drawn anime.\n\n2. **Attack on Titan**\n   - This series combines traditional hand-drawn techniques with some CGI elements, but it is primarily celebrated for its hand-drawn sequences.\n\n3. **Hunter x Hunter**\n   - Known for its detailed and dynamic fight scenes, this series is a great example of hand-drawn anime.\n\n4. **Mob Psycho 100**\n   - Directed by ONE, this series is lauded for its expressive character designs and impactful animation.\n\n5. **Natsume's Book of Friends**\n   - A beautifully drawn series with a focus on gentle, emotive storytelling.\n\n### Anime Films:\n\n1. **Spirited Away** (Studio Ghibli)\n   - Directed by Hayao Miyazaki, this film is a masterpiece of hand-drawn animation, known for its detailed and enchanting world.\n\n2. **Princess Mononoke** (Studio Ghibli)\n   - Another Miyazaki classic, this film is renowned for its intricate and beautifully rendered animation.\n\n3. **Akira**\n   - A landmark in anime, known for its groundbreaking animation and detailed futuristic setting.\n\n4. **Your Name**\n   - Directed by Makoto Shinkai, this film blends stunning visual artistry with a compelling story.\n\n5. **The Girl Who Leapt Through Time**\n   - Another work by Mamoru Hosoda, this film is cherished for its beautiful hand-drawn animation and emotional depth.\n\nThese are just a few examples; there are many other hand-drawn anime series and films out there that showcase the beauty and skill of traditional animation techniques. If you're interested in exploring more, you might also look into the works of other renowned directors and studios like Satoshi Kon, Mamoru Hosoda, and Kyoto Animation.",
